BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

1. There are 2 aluminum ions in each formula unit of aluminum selenide. The subscripts in the formula of an ionic compound tell us how many of each ion are in a formula unit of the ionic compound.

There are 3 selenide ions in each formula unit of aluminum selenide. The subscripts in the formula of an ionic compound tell us how many of each ion are in a formula unit of the ionic compound.

There are 2 moles of aluminum ions in each mole of aluminum selenide. The subscripts in the formula of an ionic compound also tell us how many moles of each ion are in a mole of the ionic compound.

There are 3 moles of selenide ions in each mole of aluminum selenide. The subscripts in the formula of an ionic compound also tell us how many moles of each ion are in a mole of the ionic compound.

2. There are 3 carbon atoms in each molecule of propane. The subscripts in the formula of a covalent compound tell us how many of each atom are in a molecule of the covalent compound.

There are 8 hydrogen atoms in each molecule of propane. The subscripts in the formula of a covalent compound tell us how many of each atom are in a molecule of the covalent compound.

There are 3 moles of carbon atoms in each mole of propane. The subscripts in the formula of a covalent compound also tell us how many moles of each atom are in a mole of the covalent compound.

There are 8 moles of hydrogen atoms in each mole of propane. The subscripts in the formula of a covalent compound also tell us how many moles of each atom are in a mole of the covalent compound.

